article.headline: Wofford 69, Davidson 64
article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- Cameron Rundles scored 22 points and had three steals to lead Wofford to a 69-64 win over Davidson on Saturday night. The Terriers (8-9, 5-1 Southern Conference) never trailed in the second half but had trouble putting Davidson away. Rundles knocked down two free throws to give Wofford a 61-53 lead with 1:22 to play. Davidson used a 9-2 run, cutting the margin to two points on Nik Cochran's 3-pointer with 46 seconds left. Wofford's Terry Martin made a free throw that put the Terriers up 67-64 with 6 seconds left. The Wildcats (8-9, 2-4) failed to tie the game when Cochran turned the ball over, helping to preserve the win for Wofford. J.P. Kuhlman led Davidson with 14 points and Cochran had 11. The Terriers shot 7 of 13 from beyond the arc.
